com.symbol.emdk.barcode

Class ScannerConfig.DecoderParams.UpcEanParams

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.symbol.emdk.barcode.ScannerConfig.DecoderParams.UpcEanParams
  • Enclosing class:
    ScannerConfig.DecoderParams

    public class ScannerConfig.DecoderParams.UpcEanParams
extends java.lang.Object
    The UPCEAN class provides access to parameters that are available for the UPC/EAN decoder. UPC/EAN is the family of codes which are used to identify products and UPC EAN Params are the params common to these codes 

     
 	Example Usage:
 	config.upcEanParams.booklandCode = true;

    • Field Detail

      • booklandCode

        public boolean booklandCode
        Flag to enable Bookland code decoding. Any EAN which begins with the 978 prefix is called a Bookland EAN barcode and is used on books and book related products internationally. 

         
 	Example Usage:
 	upcEan.booklandCode = true;

      • booklandFormat

        public ScannerConfig.BooklandFormat booklandFormat
        Specifies the bookland format to use. Use enum ScannerConfig.BooklandFormat. 

         
 	Example Usage:
 	upcEan.booklandFormat = BooklandFormat.ISBN_10;

      • convertDataBarToUpcEan

        public boolean convertDataBarToUpcEan
        If this is set it converts DataBar barcodes to UPC/EAN format. For this setting to work UPC/EAN symbologies must be enabled. A check in the checkbox indicates that the option is enabled. 

         
 	Example Usage:
 	upcEan.convertDataBarToUPCEAN = true;

      • couponCode

        public boolean couponCode
        Enables Coupon code decoding. Note that in order to successfully decode Coupon codes, all of the correct decoders must be enabled. 

         
 	Example Usage:
 	upcEan.couponCode = true;

      • linearDecode

        @Deprecated
public boolean linearDecode
        Deprecated. 

      • randomWeightCheckDigit

        public boolean randomWeightCheckDigit
        Flag to enable random weight check digit verification. 

         
 	Example Usage:
 	upcEan.randomWeightCheckDigit = true;

      • securityLevel

        public ScannerConfig.SecurityLevel securityLevel
        The scanner of fers four levels of decode security for UPC/EAN barcodes. Select higher security levels for lower quality bar codes. There is an inverse relationship between security and decode speed, so be sure to choose only that level of security necessary for the application. Use enum ScannerConfig.SecurityLevel. 

         
 	Example Usage:
 	upcEan.securityLevel = SecurityLevel.LEVEL_0;

      • supplemental2

        public boolean supplemental2
        Flag to enable length 2 supplementals. 

         
 	Example Usage:
 	upcEan.supplemental2 = false;

      • supplemental5

        public boolean supplemental5
        Flag to enable length 5 supplementals. 

         
 	Example Usage:
 	upcEan.supplemental5 = false;

      • supplementalMode

        public ScannerConfig.SupplementalMode supplementalMode
        The supplemental mode. Use enum ScannerConfig.SupplementalMode. 

         
 	Example Usage:
 	upcEan.supplementalMode = SupplementalMode.S_378_379;

      • supplementalRetries

        public int supplementalRetries
        Retry count for auto-discriminating for supplementals. Possible values are 2 to 20 inclusive. Note that this flag is only considered if Supplemental Mode - UPC EAN is set to one of the following values: Supplementals Auto, Supplementals Smart, Supplementals 378-379 , Supplementals 978-979, Supplementals 977 or Supplementals 414-419-434-439 (2 to 20, default 10). 

         
 	Example Usage:
 	upcEan.supplementalRetries = 10;

      • couponReport

        public ScannerConfig.CouponReport couponReport
        Used to differentiate between old coupon (UPC/EAN and Code128) and new GS1 DataBar Coupons. NOTE: There is an Interim GS1 DataBar Coupon (UPC A and the GS1 DataBar), which is meant for smooth transition of adaption from old coupon format to new coupon format. If an interim coupon is presented to the scanner, it will read old or new portion of it, depending on the report mode setting. Use enum ScannerConfig.CouponReport. 

         
 	Example Usage:
 	upcEan.couponReport = CouponReport.OLD;

      • eanZeroExtend

        public boolean eanZeroExtend
        Enable this parameter to add five leading zeros to decoded EAN-8 symbols to make them compatible in format to EAN-13 symbols. Disable this to transmit EAN-8 symbols as is

      • reducedQuietZone

        public boolean reducedQuietZone
        Flag to Enable or Disable decoding of UPC barcodes with reduced quiet zones. If you enable, select a OneDQuietZoneLevel to set the effort level. 

         
 	Example Usage:
 	upcEan.reducedQuietZone = true;
